By: Akka Mahadevi
Format: verse
Title: Like a River in Flood
---
Like a river
in flood
filling a dry lake floor,

Like rain
drenching dried twigs.

An inundation of delight, today,
the joy of this world
and the journey beyond -- both
Came to me, hand in hand.

O jasmine lord,
I saw the foot of the holy one today
and am whole.
